  "prompt": "Which Pakistani universities are recognized by Australian immigration department?",
  "response": "Australian immigration recognizes degrees from universities that are accredited by the Higher Education Commission (HEC) of Pakistan, provided that the institution is internationally recognized. However, for specific recognition under the **Australian Qualifications Framework (AQF)**, it's essential to check the **National Office of Overseas Skills Recognition (NOOSR)** or the **Department of Home Affairs** website for the most up-to-date and accurate information.\n\nSome well-known Pakistani universities that are generally recognized by Australian immigration (subject to verification) include:\n\n1. **Quaid-i-Azam University, Islamabad**\n2. **University of the Punjab, Lahore**\n3. **National University of Sciences and Technology (NUST), Islamabad**\n4. **Lahore University of Management Sciences (LUMS)**\n5. **Aga Khan University, Karachi**\n6. **University of Karachi**\n7. **University of Engineering and Technology (UET), Lahore**\n8. **COMSATS University Islamabad**\n9. **Bahria University**\n10. **Institute of Business Administration (IBA), Karachi**\n\nTo confirm whether a specific university or degree is recognized, applicants should:\n\n- Verify the institution's accreditation status with the **HEC Pakistan**.\n- Use the **Department of Home Affairs' qualification recognition tool** or consult with **NOOSR**.\n- Consider obtaining a **Educational Credential Assessment (ECA)** from an approved organization like **VETASSESS**, **AQA**, or **TRA**.\n\nAlways ensure that the information is up-to-date, as recognition policies may change.",
